"""Repository layer - data access, one repository per aggregate.

alchemiq already gives you a full repository per model: instantiate it ad-hoc
with ``Repository(Note)`` or subclass to attach behaviour (query helpers,
caching) under a name the rest of the app can depend on:

    from alchemiq import Repository

    from __ALCHEMIQ_MODULE__.domain.models import Note


    class NoteRepository(Repository[Note]):
        pass  # add query helpers / cache settings here

Repositories run inside whatever ``UnitOfWork`` (or ambient session) the
caller has opened - they never open their own transaction.
"""
